# Auto-build release EXE (required)

This repo ships a **Windows desktop `.exe`**. Rules do **not** run scripts by themselves — **you (Agent) must execute** the build command below before marking the task done.

## When to build

Run a build if **any** of these happened in this task (including merge, pull, or applying patches):

- `src/` (App), `ui/` (WebView UI), `scripts/build-release.ps1`, `scripts/watch-build-release.ps1`
- User merged/pulled changes that touch the above — **disk changed ⇒ treat as changed**

Do **not** skip because the task was "only git" or "only sync".

## Command (repo root, PowerShell)

```powershell
.\scripts\watch-build-release.ps1 -Once
```

Full offline folder (only when user needs `models/` in `dist/`):

```powershell
.\scripts\watch-build-release.ps1 -Once -IncludeModels
```

## After build (required in your reply)

1. Report `dist\ArrayMicRefreshment-self-contained\ArrayMicRefreshment.exe` path and **LastWriteTime**.
2. Do not assume an older `dist/` exe is still valid after App / `wwwroot` / WebView2 changes.

## User machine (not Agent — remind once if relevant)

- Commit hook: `.\scripts\install-git-hooks.ps1`
- Save watcher: `.\scripts\watch-build-release.ps1` (background)
